# EnvironmentFile for iot-sensord.service.
#
# IOT_SENSORD_ARGS is the literal argv tail passed to
# /usr/local/bin/iot-sensord. The daemon owns the I2C bus (mangOH Yellow
# BMI160 / BME680 / light sensor) and publishes the latest readings to the
# data-store under iot.sensor.* (temp, humidity, pressure, lux, accel, gyro,
# version). The lwm2m client mirrors those into IPSO objects for the cloud,
# and the device-ui shows them locally — see
# /etc/iot/ds-schemas/iot.lua and apps/docs/tdd-mangoh-yellow-sensors.md.
#
# Tunables (argv only — there is no hot-reload of the sample loop):
#   --interval=SECS   sample cadence (default 10)
#   --bme=ADDR        BME680 address (0x76 default, 0x77 if SDO high)
#   --imu=ADDR        BMI160 address (0x68 default, 0x69 if SDO high)
#   --light=ADDR      light-sensor address (0x44 default; confirm part on HW)
#   --once            sample once and exit (bring-up smoke test)
#
# Operator workflow (bare metal):
#   # confirm the bus first: i2cdetect -y 1   (expect 0x76, 0x68, 0x44, …)
#   sudo systemctl daemon-reload
#   sudo systemctl enable --now iot-sensord.service
#   ds-cli get iot.sensor.temp
#   journalctl -u iot-sensord.service -f
#
# Privilege: the daemon maps /dev/mem (CAP_SYS_RAWIO). On a kernel with
# CONFIG_STRICT_DEVMEM the peripheral pages may still be blocked — the exact
# capability/device wiring is validated on hardware (PR-4).

IOT_SENSORD_ARGS="--ds-sock=/run/iot/data_store.sock --interval=10"
